text.paragraph:
Note:  In these trials the incidence of nonserious rash was 2% for lamotrigine extended-release and 3% for placebo.  In clinical trials evaluating immediate-release lamotrigine, the rate of serious rash was 0.3% in adults on adjunctive therapy for epilepsy [see 
                              Boxed Warning
                           ].
